Subject: [PATCH 3/6] Pet window follows the cursor / Blockly monitor on multi-display setups

Upstream's `continueSetWindowModePet()` in `src/main/window-manager.ts`
currently computes a bounding rectangle across ALL connected displays
and sizes the pet window to cover the full virtual screen. On a
multi-monitor Maker Lab setup this means:

  - The transparent click-through region spans every display, which
    causes some X11 compositors to disable transparency for the full
    window (entire rectangle goes opaque).
  - The Live2D canvas is centered in the virtual-screen bounding box,
    which may land in empty space between monitors with mismatched
    geometries.

Fix: on pet-mode entry, pick the display that either (a) currently
contains the cursor, or (b) contains the Blockly kiosk window (queried
via the existing BrowserWindow list), and size the pet window to that
single display's bounds. Fall back to the primary display.

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932

TODO(Phase 3.1): fill in hunks. Touch points (line numbers pinned to
current SHA):
- src/main/window-manager.ts lines 204-225 — replace the
  `Math.min(...getAllDisplays())` bounding-box computation with a
  `chooseTargetDisplay()` helper that prefers cursor / Blockly / primary.
- src/main/window-manager.ts — import `screen.getCursorScreenPoint`
  and `screen.getDisplayNearestPoint` (already partially imported).
